  "texts": [
    "The Cloud Pool consists of 20 servers hosting large models (LLaMA2-70B, LLaMA3-70B, Qwen-72B) distributed across 4×A100, 4×H100, and 4×A6000 configurations.",
    "The Edge Pool contains 600 GPUs (300 A40s and 300 V100s) evenly serving LLaMA-2-7B, Qwen-7B, and LLaMA-3.1-8B draft models.",
    "All experiments run over a 10 ms RTT network connection.",
    "The scheduler exposes three knobs: Routing (Random vs. JSQ); Queueing (FIFO vs. Length-Aware Batching, or LAB, which groups requests of similar lengths to minimize padding); and Window Control (Static γ = 4, Dynamic γ, and AWC).",
    "Accumulating these policies yields steady improvements in both throughput and latency."
